<p><b>What are the three categories of auditing standards?</b> Generally accepted auditing standards are detailed in three sections labeled General Standards, Standards of Fieldwork, and Standards of Reporting.</p>
<p><b>What is standard audit process?</b> Although every audit process is unique, the audit process is similar for most engagements and normally consists of four stages: Planning (sometimes called Survey or Preliminary Review), Fieldwork, Audit Report and Follow-up Review.</p>
<p><b>What is ISA standards in audit?</b> International Standards on Auditing (ISA) are professional standards for the auditing of financial information. These standards are issued by the International Auditing and Assurance Standards Board (IAASB).</p>